{"_id":"3b545d3f088c54e9","name":"LoTM Rules Reference","pages":[{"_id":"20873b5087fb7733","name":"Table of Contents","type":"text","text":{"content":"<h1>LoTM Rules Reference</h1><p>This journal mirrors core rulebook sections for in-game lookup.</p><h2>Table of Contents</h2><ol><li><a href='#checks'>Checks and Targets</a></li><li><a href='#combat'>Combat and Action Economy</a></li><li><a href='#corruption'>Corruption and Threshold Events</a></li><li><a href='#advancement'>Advancement Sequence 9 to 0</a></li><li><a href='#rituals'>Ritual Casting</a></li><li><a href='#artifacts'>Sealed Artifacts</a></li><li><a href='#conditions'>Conditions and Effects</a></li></ol><hr /><h2 id='checks'>Checks and Targets</h2><p>Roll 1d100 and succeed when roll is less than or equal to final target. Final target is clamped to 1..95.</p><h2 id='combat'>Combat and Action Economy</h2><p>Baseline turn budget is 1 Action, 1 Move, and 1 Reaction per round. Damage and attack formulas are defined in system config and automation cards.</p><h2 id='corruption'>Corruption and Threshold Events</h2><p>Corruption applies universal penalties by 10% bands and triggers events at 30, 60, 90, and 100 percent.</p><h2 id='advancement'>Advancement Sequence 9 to 0</h2><p>Advancement follows Preparation, Channeling, Integration with pass/fail consequences and backlash rules.</p><h2 id='rituals'>Ritual Casting</h2><p>Rituals use complexity classes and mandatory components. Universal rituals can be used by any pathway when prerequisites are met.</p><h2 id='artifacts'>Sealed Artifacts</h2><p>Artifact risk classes are stable, volatile, and catastrophic. Misuse can trigger backlash and corruption gain.</p><h2 id='conditions'>Conditions and Effects</h2><p>Conditions map to deterministic effect paths and save semantics defined in condition library and schema contracts.</p>","format":1},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}},{"_id":"37551bd0256db52e","name":"Automation Notes","type":"text","text":{"content":"<h2>Foundry Automation Boundaries</h2><ul><li><strong>Automated:</strong> check cards, damage calculations, corruption penalties, ritual risk rolls, artifact backlash rolls.</li><li><strong>Manual:</strong> narrative adjudication, non-codified edge effects, hidden GM interpretation.</li></ul><p>Use compendium packs for pathway data, abilities, items, rituals, artifacts, roll tables, and NPC archetypes.</p>","format":1},"sort":10,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{}}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"flags":{"lotm":{"contentId":"rules.reference.core","version":"1.2.2","minSystemVersion":"1.2.2","maxTestedSystemVersion":"1.2.12","dependencies":[],"groups":{"category":"rules-reference"}}}}
